### 2. Material: Aluminum vs. Stainless Steel

The classic Moka Express is aluminum, which is the gold standard for heat transfer and flavor development. However, if you have an induction stovetop, you must opt for the Bialetti Venus or Moka Induction models, which are made of stainless steel. While the stainless steel versions are induction-compatible and dishwasher-safe, many purists argue the aluminum pot provides a slightly superior, more traditional flavor profile due to its seasoning properties.

### Cleaning and Care

To maintain your Moka Express, simply rinse all parts with warm water after each use. Never use soap or abrasive sponges, as this strips the aluminum of its protective, flavor-enhancing patina. Allow the parts to air dry completely before reassembling to prevent oxidation. For a deeper clean, you can occasionally brew a batch of water only, or use a mixture of water and white vinegar to remove mineral buildup.

